OL,3,CTiny typo costs Bristol council tax
OL,4,Cpayers almost #200,000
OL,6,FThe councils "typographical error"
OL,7,Fsaid it was the other way around: 5.9
OL,8,Fper cent for the commissioner and five
OL,9,Fper cent for the fire authority. The
OL,10,Foverall council tax bill had no
OL,11,Fmathematical error, but council still
OL,12,Fhad to write to households explaining
OL,13,Ftheir mistake.
OL,15,FPrinting and posting these letters
OL,16,Fcost the council #198,000.
OL,18,FLabour Councillor Don Alexander and
OL,19,FLiberal Democrat Cllr Nicholas Coombes
OL,20,Fpressed for details during meeting on
OL,21,F4 November.
