OL,3,CTiny typo costs Bristol council tax
OL,4,Cpayers almost #200,000
OL,6,FThe letter was written by the
OL,7,Fcouncil's head of revenue and
OL,8,Fbenefits, Graham Clapp, and apologised
OL,9,Ffor the mistake but explained the
OL,10,Ferror had no impact on the bill at all.
OL,12,FIn the letter, Mr Clapp said: "It has
OL,13,Fcome to light that there is a
OL,14,Ftypographical error contained within
OL,15,Fthe council tax bill issued to you
OL,16,Fthis year. This error has now been
OL,17,Fcorrected but we are required by law
OL,18,Fto write to those who received a bill
OL,19,Fwith this error, to both highlight the
OL,20,Ferror and explain the steps we have
OL,21,Ftaken to correct this.
OL,26,@tD@_OU
